01:24:09,928 --> 01:24:13,591
"Try refusing a million times,
"You're in love, my love"

590
01:24:19,805 --> 01:24:23,639
"Try refusing a million times,
but you're in love"

591
01:24:24,109 --> 01:24:28,170
"Darling, this is love"

592
01:25:04,316 --> 01:25:09,117
"What's come over..."

593
01:25:11,122 --> 01:25:13,056
"my heart?"

594
01:25:15,393 --> 01:25:19,659
"My heart was with me always"

595
01:25:19,865 --> 01:25:23,665
"Have I lost it?"

596
01:25:25,871 --> 01:25:27,805
"I've lost it"

597
01:25:46,791 --> 01:25:49,385
Ma, you remember the dream
I wrote about in my diary?

598
01:25:51,196 --> 01:25:54,256
That face I imagined
holding in my hands?

599
01:25:56,067 --> 01:25:58,035
The one, I wanted to face

600
01:25:59,938 --> 01:26:02,031
I've found him

601
01:26:03,241 --> 01:26:05,175
What...?

602
01:26:05,977 --> 01:26:10,710
What are you saying, Simi?
- Yes Ma. When I was leaving...

603
01:26:10,849 --> 01:26:13,113
I was clear about what
I was getting out of life

604
01:26:13,919 --> 01:26:18,856
For a month, I wanted to be as happy
as I could. Then I'd come back...

605
01:26:19,324 --> 01:26:23,988
and go away to my country to spend
a lifetime with a stranger

606
01:26:24,930 --> 01:26:29,993
I had come to a compromise with my
destiny, Ma. But little did I know...

607
01:26:30,936 --> 01:26:35,134
this was in store for me.
Like a storm he came...

608
01:26:36,074 --> 01:26:38,907
and he swept me off
like a fallen leaf

609
01:26:42,981 --> 01:26:46,314
Love's like this, like that,
I had read, I had heard

610
01:26:47,252 --> 01:26:52,656
But I never understood. When, for the
first time, he offered me his hand...

611
01:26:52,791 --> 01:26:56,659
I still didn't understand.
I was with him for so long...

612
01:26:57,996 --> 01:27:04,196
still I didn't understand anything.
But today, when we were parting...

613
01:27:05,870 --> 01:27:10,136
for the first time I felt
that afterthis moment...

614
01:27:11,076 --> 01:27:17,311
I'm not going to see him ever again.
I kept looking back. He was going away

615
01:27:18,683 --> 01:27:23,620
I wanted to stop him, I wanted to say
something, I wanted to hear something

616
01:27:25,857 --> 01:27:30,920
But he didn't stop. I understood.
This is what love is like

617
01:27:32,864 --> 01:27:39,667
And to him, I've given all my dreams.
I don't even know whether he loves me

618
01:27:41,006 --> 01:27:46,808
All I know is that for me, he's life.
I can never be anyone else's, Ma

619
01:28:04,329 --> 01:28:07,127
You're up? Simi and I
have been talking

620
01:28:07,799 --> 01:28:10,666
She's back after so long.
I even lost track of time

621
01:28:27,285 --> 01:28:31,813
I told you, not to betray my trust

622
01:28:34,893 --> 01:28:39,830
I took a promise from you.
And you've deceived me?

623
01:28:40,632 --> 01:28:42,827
No Babuji...
- Listen, first ask her

624
01:28:43,034 --> 01:28:45,002
I don't want to listen to anything!

625
01:28:47,338 --> 01:28:51,866
Pack. Tomorrow morning,
we leave for India

626
01:28:54,079 --> 01:28:55,603
For good

627
01:29:01,820 --> 01:29:03,754
Let her cry

628
01:29:04,222 --> 01:29:06,747
She has writ it on her own destiny

629
01:29:08,093 --> 01:29:11,756
She will have to learn for herself
how to get over it. Let her cry

630
01:29:49,434 --> 01:29:51,368
What's her name?
- Simran

631
01:29:54,172 --> 01:29:56,106
What girl, Pops?

632
01:29:57,175 --> 01:29:59,837
The one whose face you see
in the moon.

633
01:30:01,045 --> 01:30:03,240
I'm not one of them...

634
01:30:03,414 --> 01:30:06,110
who will go crazy about a girl.
- Yes, I forgot!

635
01:30:06,451 --> 01:30:09,284
Some have good lips, some have
beautiful eyes...

636
01:30:13,024 --> 01:30:14,958
Lives where?
- Who, Pops?

637
01:30:17,028 --> 01:30:18,962
This... Simran

638
01:30:24,302 --> 01:30:27,965
Don't know
- How is she?

639
01:30:29,774 --> 01:30:31,708
Very lovable

640
01:30:33,311 --> 01:30:35,245
Then what's the problem?

641
01:30:36,314 --> 01:30:41,980
Problem is, she's about to marry.
- How about stopping the wedding?

642
01:30:44,189 --> 01:30:47,249
In yourtimes, it was different.
Times have changed

643
01:30:49,494 --> 01:30:54,761
Love is still called "love". That has
never changed, nor will it ever change

644
01:30:57,835 --> 01:31:01,430
She's going to be someone else's.
- The bride goes to the man...

645
01:31:01,773 --> 01:31:08,042
who brings her home. I didn't sire
you to play that fiddle. We aren't...

646
01:31:08,179 --> 01:31:10,079
those who stare at the moon. You
reach out to the moon...

647
01:31:10,215 --> 01:31:12,149
you bring her home. Go

648
01:31:13,184 --> 01:31:15,982
And come home only
with your bride. Get it?

649
01:32:00,265 --> 01:32:03,063
Gone. The daughter is
getting married.

650
01:32:03,268 --> 01:32:05,202
They've sold out and moved to Punjab

651
01:32:34,265 --> 01:32:36,199
I'm coming, Simran

652
01:32:38,136 --> 01:32:40,070
I'm coming

653
01:33:42,966 --> 01:33:47,994
"When the girls go to the riverbank,
you'll hear their anklets chime"

654
01:33:48,672 --> 01:33:51,004
"When the ripe mustard sways
in the farms..."

655
01:33:51,208 --> 01:33:53,267
"you'll know a year
has come to pass"

656
01:33:55,812 --> 01:34:00,749
"Come today, come with a smile,
bring me a song, I've been waiting..."

657
01:34:01,151 --> 01:34:05,747
"for the whistle
of the chugging train"

658
01:34:06,823 --> 01:34:10,953
"Come home o'wanderer,
your mate beckons"

659
01:34:12,028 --> 01:34:13,996
"Come home o'wanderer"

660
01:34:18,034 --> 01:34:21,128
"Your land beckons"

661
01:34:41,825 --> 01:34:43,759
Bless me, Ma-ji

662
01:34:53,236 --> 01:34:55,295
No Ma-ji

663
01:34:58,375 --> 01:35:05,213
Son, 20 years I've held back
these tears

664
01:35:09,753 --> 01:35:14,156
Today, they won't stop, son.
Not today

665
01:35:20,831 --> 01:35:22,765
Simran, my child

666
01:35:23,233 --> 01:35:25,167
My baby doll

667
01:35:29,973 --> 01:35:32,771
How have you been?
- I haven't changed a bit!

668
01:35:33,243 --> 01:35:37,646
You're the bride's aunt now!
Time to find a good groom for yourself

669
01:35:37,848 --> 01:35:40,817
Lajjo, I've been ready all these years!
But in this village...

670
01:35:40,951 --> 01:35:44,910
there isn't one who's a match for me.
So what do I do? For me, I think...

671
01:35:45,088 --> 01:35:48,956
it'll have to be a foreigner!
- You haven't changed a bit

672
01:35:49,092 --> 01:35:50,821
Not a bit!

673
01:35:51,294 --> 01:35:55,822
You did keep us waiting.
Anyway, better late than never

674
01:35:56,032 --> 01:35:59,092
Wife, will you excuse us a moment?
- Get lost

675
01:36:03,039 --> 01:36:05,974
Come on. Baldev, who's this?
Go on...

676
01:36:07,043 --> 01:36:10,103
You don't know?
My daughter Preeti

677
01:36:10,447 --> 01:36:13,780
Kuljit's sister.
- May you live long

678
01:36:15,719 --> 01:36:19,052
Wonderful, isn't it? In 20 years,
the whole generation has come of age

679
01:36:19,990 --> 01:36:21,355
She's beautiful.
- Father's daughter, right?

680
01:36:22,092 --> 01:36:23,650
Get lost

681
01:36:23,994 --> 01:36:25,655
Where's Kuljit?
- Yes, where's Kuljit?

682
01:36:25,996 --> 01:36:28,692
Bhaiyya (Brother) is out for a hunt.
He should be back soon

683
01:36:53,156 --> 01:36:55,090
My respects.
- May you live long, son

684
01:36:55,659 --> 01:36:57,388
My respects.
- May you live long, son

685
01:36:59,663 --> 01:37:03,724
That's a strong lad from Punjab.
- Whose son is he anyway?

686
01:37:03,934 --> 01:37:05,299
Get lost

687
01:37:05,669 --> 01:37:08,638
Come, breakfast is ready.
- Yes hurry. I'm famished

688
01:37:08,805 --> 01:37:10,705
Come on kids

689
01:37:11,041 --> 01:37:15,239
For you, for you and for you

690
01:37:15,779 --> 01:37:17,713
You must take me out
tomorrow morning.

691
01:37:18,048 --> 01:37:19,709
Sure Didi (Sister)

692
01:37:49,379 --> 01:37:51,779
Kids, Grannie wants
everyone downstairs

693
01:38:12,802 --> 01:38:18,263
You know Simi, when I was a kid,
my father would tell me...

694
01:38:19,676 --> 01:38:26,013
there's no difference between
man and woman. All have equal rights

695
01:38:27,951 --> 01:38:33,048
All my childhood, I lived believing
it's true. But as I grew up...

696
01:38:34,724 --> 01:38:36,783
I realised what a lie that is

697
01:38:39,729 --> 01:38:42,789
I wasn't given an education,
because it was more important...

698
01:38:42,932 --> 01:38:47,062
that my brothers be educated.
That was my first sacrifice

699
01:38:49,139 --> 01:38:53,337
Then, at every step, sometimes
as daughter, sometimes as sister...

700
01:38:54,144 --> 01:38:56,669
sometimes as wife... I went on
sacrificing my own happiness

701
01:38:59,749 --> 01:39:01,683
But once you were born...

702
01:39:02,752 --> 01:39:05,220
when I held you in my hands
for the first time...

703
01:39:06,890 --> 01:39:14,729
I made a promise, never to let happen
to my daughter, what happened to me

704
01:39:16,800 --> 01:39:21,396
No more sacrifices at every step
as daughter, as sister, as wife

705
01:39:23,105 --> 01:39:27,303
So what if she's a girl?
She'd live her life as she wishes

706
01:39:28,376 --> 01:39:33,439
She'd have her share of happiness.
But I was wrong, Simran

707
01:39:34,850 --> 01:39:39,048
I had even forgotten that a woman
hasn't even the right to make promises

708
